()AfterProvisioning kya hai kya karta hai?
--🔹 AfterProvisioning Rule kya hai?
👉 SailPoint IdentityIQ me:-
AfterProvisioning Rule ek post-processing rule hoti hai jo tab run hoti hai jab provisioning process successfully complete ho jata hai.

🔹 Simple Samajh (Flow):-
Access Request / Identity Refresh
        ↓
ProvisioningPlan create
        ↓
BeforeProvisioning Rule  🔥
        ↓
Provisioning (AD, DB, etc.) execute
        ↓
AfterProvisioning Rule  🔥 (yaha tera rule chalta hai).

🔹 AfterProvisioning ka main purpose:-
1️⃣ 📊 Logging & Audit:-
Kaun sa account create hua
Kaun se attributes set hue
Kaun si application me provisioning hui
👉 Example:-
AD account created → log store
Compliance ke liye tracking

2️⃣ 📧 Notification:-
Email to user / manager / admin
Slack / webhook alerts
👉 Example:-
“Your account has been created”
“Provisioning failed for user”

3️⃣ 🔍 Result Validation:-
Check provisioning success/failure
Analyze provisioning errors
👉 Example:-
AD failed → error log
DB update failed → retry logic trigger

4️⃣ 🧹 Post Processing:-
Extra attributes update
Custom database update
External system call
👉 Example:-
EmployeeId ko CRM me update karna
Custom logging system me entry

5️⃣ ⚠️ Error Handling:-
👉 Provisioning process me:-
AD / DB / LDAP call fail ho sakta hai
Attribute set nahi ho pata
Network / API issue aa sakta hai
👉 AfterProvisioning me tu:-
Result check karta hai
Errors identify karta hai
Actions leta hai (log, alert, retry).
----------------------------------------------
<Rule name="AfterProvisioning_ErrorHandling" type="AfterProvisioning">
    <Source>

        import sailpoint.api.SailPointContext;
        import sailpoint.object.ProvisioningPlan;
        import sailpoint.object.AccountRequest;
        import sailpoint.object.AttributeRequest;
        import sailpoint.object.ProvisioningResult;
        import java.util.List;

        SailPointContext context = (SailPointContext) args.get("context");
        ProvisioningPlan plan = (ProvisioningPlan) args.get("plan");

        if (plan == null) {
            System.out.println("Provisioning plan is null");
            return;
        }

        List accountRequests = plan.getAccountRequests();

        if (accountRequests != null) {

            for (Object obj : accountRequests) {

                AccountRequest accReq = (AccountRequest) obj;

                // 🔹 Get result object (important for error handling)
                ProvisioningResult result = accReq.getResult();

                if (result == null) {
                    System.out.println("Result is null for account: " + accReq.getNativeIdentity());
                    continue;
                }

                String status = result.getStatus();

                System.out.println("Account: " + accReq.getNativeIdentity());
                System.out.println("Status: " + status);

                // 🔥 ERROR HANDLING
                if ("FAILED".equalsIgnoreCase(status)) {

                    System.out.println("Provisioning failed!");

                    // Get errors
                    List errors = result.getErrors();

                    if (errors != null) {
                        for (Object err : errors) {
                            System.out.println("Error: " + err.toString());
                        }
                    }

                    // 🔥 Custom handling (example)
                    // 1. Log
                    // 2. Send alert
                    // 3. Store in DB
                    System.out.println("Taking action for failure...");
                }

                // 🔥 SUCCESS HANDLING
                else if ("COMPLETED".equalsIgnoreCase(status)) {
                    System.out.println("Provisioning successful");

                    // Example: audit log
                    System.out.println("Account created successfully: " + accReq.getNativeIdentity());
                }
            }
        }

        System.out.println("AfterProvisioning Error Handling completed");

    </Source>
</Rule>
//////////*
()🔹 1️⃣ continue ka matlab kya hai?
👉 continue ek loop control statement hai (Java/BeanShell me)

✅ Iska kaam:-
👉 current iteration ko skip karna aur next iteration par jaana

🔹 Tumhara code:-
if (result == null) {
    System.out.println("Result is null for account: " + accReq.getNativeIdentity());
    continue;
}
👉 Matlab:-
Agar result == null hai
To:-
log print karo
aur iss account ko process karna skip karo
loop next account par chala jayega
-----------------------------------------------
🔹 2️⃣ args kya hai?
👉 args ek Map object hota hai jo SailPoint rule engine pass karta hai
🔹 Real meaning:-
👉 SailPoint IdentityIQ rule execute karte time:-
SailPoint system automatically:
context
provisioningPlan
identity
aur dusri values
👉 sab args ke through pass karta hai.

🔹 args kaha se aata hai?
👉 Ye developer nahi banata
👉 Ye SailPoint engine internally create karta hai
*//////////
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<!DOCTYPE Rule PUBLIC "sailpoint.dtd" "sailpoint.dtd">
<Rule language="beanshell" name="Global-AfterProvisioning-Rule" type="AfterProvisioning">
  <Source>
  <![CDATA[
  import sailpoint.object.*;
  import sailpoint.api.ProvisioningPlan;
  import sailpoint.api.ProvisioningPlan.AccountRequest;
  import sailpoint.api.ProvisioningPlan.AttributeRequest;
  import org.apache.commons.logging.Log;
  import org.apache.commons.logging.LogFactory;

  Log customLogger = LogFactory.getLog(this.getClass());

  if (plan != null) {
      // 1. Result Check: Kya provisioning sach mein successful hui?
      ProvisioningResult result = plan.getResult();
      
      if (result != null && ProvisioningResult.STATUS_COMMITTED.equals(result.getStatus())) {
          
          List accReqs = plan.getAccountRequests();
          for (AccountRequest accReq : accReqs) {
              
              // 2. Sirf 'Create' operation ke baad welcome mail trigger karna
              if (AccountRequest.Operation.Create.equals(accReq.getOperation())) {
                  
                  String appName = accReq.getApplicationName();
                  String nativeIdentity = accReq.getNativeIdentity(); // AD ka DN ya ID
                  
                  customLogger.info("Success! Account created in " + appName + " with ID: " + nativeIdentity);

                  // 3. Post-Creation Logic: Triggering an Email
                  Identity user = plan.getIdentity();
                  if (user != null) {
                      String userEmail = user.getEmail();
                      if (userEmail != null) {
                          // Production mein yahan Email Template call hota hai
                          customLogger.info("Triggering Welcome Email to: " + userEmail);
                      }
                  }
              }
          }
      } else {
          customLogger.error("Provisioning failed or is still in 'Pending' state.");
      }
  }
  ]]>
  </Source>
</Rule>
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
